post_text:
Academy ISD Parents and Guardians,

If you have not yet verified enrollment for your child for next year, please make sure to do so online this week. If you have a new student or know someone who is new to the district, next week Academy ISD will have in-person open enrollment for new and returning students on Tuesday, August 4th and Wednesday, August 5th. Hours of operation will be 9:00AM - 12:00PM and 3:00PM - 6:00PM at Academy High School. For additional information regarding enrollment and required documents please see the Academy ISD website.

Also, Academy ISD will be sending out a preliminary choice survey for decisions regarding returning to school, and then two weeks prior to the actual start of school, you will finalize your child‚Äôs options. Your preliminary choices right now will assist us with detailed preparations for both remote and on-campus instruction as well as child nutrition, transportation, and technology.

Thank you for your participation!

AISD Administration

The Academy Independent School District (ISD) Board of Trustees has employed Texas Association of School Boards (TASB) Executive Search Services to assist with the search for a new superintendent. This survey will close at midnight on May 29, 2019.

Dear AISD families,

All campuses received STAAR scores for 3rd through 8th graders from the May testing administration.

You can access your student‚Äôs scores online.
The following link will take you to the Texas Assessment Website.

http://texasassessment.com/

To log in and view your student‚Äôs assessment results, it will ask you to enter your six-character Unique Access Code and the student's date of birth that appears on your most recent STAAR Report Card.
The code must be entered exactly as it appears.

If you can‚Äôt locate your access code, please select ‚ÄúLook Up Access Code.‚Äù You will then be asked for your student‚Äôs PEIMS ID number. In most cases, this is your student‚Äôs social security number.

shared_text:
Academy ISD Band
March 20, 2018 at 2:54 PM ¬∑ Little River-Academy, TX ¬∑

I thought I would share a group photo of the band's trip to Disney over spring break. We had an incredible time! The last night we had a clinic / performance with a staff composer in the Disney Studio. It started at 9pm and lasted 2.5 hours! I thought after 3 days in the parks the kids would fall asleep on him. Boy, did they fool me, they were AWESOME. We recorded 2 songs and one was set to video from the movie "Tangled". I wish I could share it with you, I had to sign 4 pages of releases that said I wouldn't.

Anyway, I just wanted to tell you how proud I was and how well they represented our school.

post_text: Did you know? (Before the UIL) The Lady Bees played in the "Golden Girls State Championship" in 1948 where they lost to Fredericksburg 16-13. There were 30 schools of all sizes represented at the tournament. The following year, they lost in the semi-finals to Uvalde. That year there were 55 total teams. The Lady Bee heritage stretches way back! Sting 'Em!

Dear AISD families,

All campuses received STAAR scores for 3rd through 8th graders from the May testing administration. At this time, individual score reports are not available from TEA until early July.

In the meantime, you can access your student‚Äôs scores online.
The following link will take you to the Texas Assessment Website.

http://texasassessment.com/

To log in and view your student‚Äôs assessment results, it will ask you to enter your six-character Unique Access Code and the student's date of birth that appears on your most recent STAAR Report Card.
The code must be entered exactly as it appears.

If you can‚Äôt locate your access code, please select ‚ÄúLook Up Access Code.‚Äù You will then be asked for your student‚Äôs PEIMS ID number. In most cases, this is your student‚Äôs social security number.

Important Safety Information:

Yesterday, September 20th, an attempted child abduction was reported at an Academy ISD bus stop in Echo Village. At Academy, we take the safety of our students very seriously. All bus drivers and staff members have been alerted and prompted to report any suspicious activity. Each campus spoke with students about potential dangers in regards to strangers when in a public setting. We urge parents and families to discuss what to do in a situation like this with your students. Please contact your student's campus counselor if you have any questions about how to discuss this very important topic with your student.
#KeepOurBeesSafe

IMPORTANT INFO:
The results for the STAAR spring 2016 grades 3-8 administration were scheduled to be reported to districts on Wednesday, June 15, 2016. This date has been moved to Tuesday, July 5, 2016. Due to ongoing issues and concerns with reporting, The Texas Education Agency (TEA) has requested that ETS conduct additional quality control checks and verifications to ensure that results for all students for which answer documents or online records were submitted are reported error-free and attributed to the correct campus and district. The Texas Education Agency apologizes for this delay and understands the significant inconvenience late reporting will cause students, parents, teachers, and school district personnel.

post_text:
Dear Parents,
As most of you know, Little River-Academy Police Chief Lee Dixon tragically died in the line of duty last week. Over the years, Academy ISD has worked very closely with our local law enforcement to keep our schools safe. City officials have asked that we share with our school community the plans for the funeral procession. Following the service Tomorrow at Temple Bible Church, the procession will come in on HWY 95 and turn on FM 436 on its way to the Expo Center. Anyone wishing to pay their respects to Chief Dixon is encouraged to line up on the walking trail as the procession passes through Academy somewhere between 10:45 & 11:15 am.
text:
Dear Parents,
As most of you know, Little River-Academy Police Chief Lee Dixon tragically died in the line of duty last week. Over the years, Academy ISD has worked very closely with our local law enforcement to keep our schools safe. City officials have asked that we share with our school community the plans for the funeral procession. Following the service Tomorrow at Temple Bible Church, the procession will come in on HWY 95 and turn on FM 436 on its way to the Expo Center. Anyone wishing to pay their respects to Chief Dixon is encouraged to line up on the walking trail as the procession passes through Academy somewhere between 10:45 & 11:15 am.

post_text:
Friday, Feb 7 (10:25 am)
Parents,
We are continuing to monitor the weather, but at this time our plan is to continue with a normal school day. According to some weather forecasts, the temperature is supposed to climb above freezing around the time that school is out at 3:30. We will stay in contact with local officials about the road & bridge conditions. Our buses will avoid all bridges that we can possibly avoid and will drive at a much slower speed. In addition, we may even decide to hold the buses for a few minutes (maybe 4:00) before we send them on the route. If you have a concern about your child arriving home later than usual, you are more than welcome to pick them up at school.
text:
Friday, Feb 7 (10:25 am)
Parents,
We are continuing to monitor the weather, but at this time our plan is to continue with a normal school day. According to some weather forecasts, the temperature is supposed to climb above freezing around the time that school is out at 3:30. We will stay in contact with local officials about the road & bridge conditions. Our buses will avoid all bridges that we can possibly avoid and will drive at a much slower speed. In addition, we may even decide to hold the buses for a few minutes (maybe 4:00) before we send them on the route. If you have a concern about your child arriving home later than usual, you are more than welcome to pick them up at school.

The trophy area is filled to the brim with 2002-2012 varsity 1st place trophies :) if you are interested in going through these trophies to have a keepsake, please contact Linda Barganier at Linda.barganier@academyisd.net by September 1st :)

post_text: Don Eddy basketball camp will be at Academy High School gym, starting Monday, June 11 - Friday, June 15. Camp times are 8:30-4:00. Cost is $195, but Academy ISD students get $30 off, so final price is $165 for a week long all day camp. Even though registration deadline has passed, they will allow walk-up registrations without late fee this year in order to build the numbers. Please pass the word to others.
